
[1]poniard

   PONIARD, n. pon'yard. [L. pugnus.] A small dagger; a pointed instrument
   for stabbing, borne in the hand or at the girdle, or in the pocket.

   PONIARD, v.t. pon'yard. To pierce with a poniard; to stab.
